column1: # The site was known as "Bransdale No. 7" until 1953, becoming "Farndale No. 7" from 1954 onwards.
# The rainfall sheet for this gauge for the 1931-1940 decade is missing from the Met Office archive volumes.
# Annual totals for 1939 and 1940 have been taken from British Rainfall almanacs.
# Based on other HULL-WW sites, the missing sheet probably also had readings for 1934-1938, that were only submitted in 1939.
# Consequently, there are no annual totals printed for this site in the British Rainfall almanac for 1934 to 1938.
# Readings for the following periods are apportioned:
# The readings for February and March 1947 are estimated for snow and have been retained.
# These readings are estimates and have been omitted:
